The paper deals with algorithmic problems related to graph theory, specifically the Longest Detour and Exact Detour problems. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses insights from structural graph theory, which could place it in the cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) sub-category. The use of algorithms and computational complexity analysis suggests that the paper could also belong to the cs.CG (Computational Geometry) sub-category. The study of paths and distances in graphs could also place the paper in the cs.GT (Graph Theory) sub-category. Finally, the use of randomized and deterministic algorithms suggests that the paper could belong to the cs.CC (Computational Complexity) sub-category.
